description:
This course is designed to assist and prepare military veterans to successfully transition from active service to meaningful careers at companies and organizations that match their strengths and interests. This course is taught through the Four Block Foundation as well as at Fordham University.

The course is broken up into three main sections:

- Become Headstrong: Make educated decisions on potential career paths.

- Develop Your Plan: Develop a relationship-based career development strategy.

- Execute Your Plan: Develop the fundamentals of your career development and job search.
title: Military Transition & Veteran Career Development
